figures including the Venetian nun and political theorist Archangela Tarabotti, the French feminist writer Hortense Allart, and others in a study that closely examines the material bases-manuscripts, letters, books, archives, and bodies-of writing as generators of social relations that organize and conserve knowledge in particular political arrangements. In her highly original study Jed reorganizes republicanism in history, providing a new theoretical framework for understanding the work of the scholar and the social structures of archives, libraries, and erudition in which she is inscribed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aItalian literaturexHistory and criticismx16th century. 0aItalian literaturey16th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturexHistoryx16th centuryxItaly. 0aPolitics and literaturezItalyxHistoryy16th century. 0aRepublicanism in literature. 0aRepublicanismxHistoryx16th centuryxItalyxFlorence. 0aRepublicanismxHistoryxItalyxItalyxFlorence. 0aRepublicanismxHistory. 0aRepublicanismzItalyzFlorencexHistoryy16th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950054423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520950054.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles